HEADWORD: Anachorism
<hw>An*ach"o*rism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'ana`</grk> + <grk>chw^ros</grk> place.]</ety> <def>An error in
regard to the place of an event or a thing; a referring something to a
wrong place.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

